title: species in bacteria

Though genus and phylum are more commonly used in microbiology, It has been proposed that a prokaryote whose 16S ribosomal RNA sequence differs by more than 3% from that of all other organisms (that is, the sequence is less than 97% identical to any other sequence in the databases), should be considered a new species.
